  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drought Response in Diyala Governate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam in Iraq is requesting GBP 100K (20% loan) to deliver multi -purpose cash assistance (MPCA) to 215 smallholder farming households in Muqdadiya District (Wojehiya and Mahaya sub -districts) in Diyala to prevent further backsliding into poverty and rural to urban migration to seek new livelihood opportunities (Component 1). In parallel, Oxfam will map urgent needs with local government authorities and community to design a medium -term drought response (Component 2) and build on its policy, advocacy, and communication work to generate financial support from donors (Component 3).</narrative>
  </description>
